[h3 id=TutorialOnObtainingYoutubeApiCredentials 
	" Tutorial on obtaining Youtube API credentials.
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Go to the 
	[a href=https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/dashboard rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"Google Cloud Console
	]a
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Create a new project (any name, no organization).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Go to Library and enable 
	[b 
		"YouTube Data API v3
	]b
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Go to Credentials.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Configure consent screen: External. Hit Create.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"App name: ytu.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"User support email: Your email.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Developer contact: Your email.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Save and continue, twice.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Test users: Add users. Use your email and hit Add.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Save and continue.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Go to Credentials.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Create credentials: OAuth client ID.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Application type: Web application.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Name: use any name.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Authorised redirect URIs: Add URI, 
	[a href=https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Create.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Don't close the page/tab.
	$LF
]div
[hr 
]hr
[div class=p 
	"Go to 
	[a href=https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Hit the gear button on the right (OAuth 2.0 Configuration)
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Force prompt: No.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Check Use your own OAuth credentials.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Copypaste Client ID and Client secret from the google console page above.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Close the configuration dialog.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"On the left you will see Step 1 Select & authorize APIs.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Click YouTube Data API v3, select 
	[a href=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube
	]a
	" and possibly 
	[a href=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube.upload rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/youtube.upload
	]a
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Hit Authorize APIs.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You will see the "Choose an account to continue to ytu" dialog. Select your youtube channel (NOT your gmail account). If you're doing this for your brand account, pick that instead.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You will see the "Google hasnâ€™t verified this app" dialog. Hit Continue.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"You will see the "ytu wants access to your Google Account" dialog. Hit Continue. If there are checkboxes, tick them.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Hit Exchange authorization code for tokens.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Grab your Refresh token and use it. "Step 2 Exchange authorization code for tokens" automatically collapses, you will need to expand it to see the token.
]div
